{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9232ea02-0f27-4536-96ba-a1eced56ea0b","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFix: reorder so `Domain.fs` comes first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_lj1lgiPm2E7xEkgxficiMT","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-32e7963271c4478dbb1b8137572151de/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-32e7963271c4478dbb1b8137572151de/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"9881aba8-eb99-4933-a699-971c3613b9d8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, meaning it depends on `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` comes after `Services.fs` in the compile order, the compiler hasn't seen it yet when compiling `Services.fs`.\n\nThe fix is to reorder so that `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":494,"requestId":"1C42:11A36E:B6C361:D3BEB1:69F3FA6E"},"id":"29bfdab4-83cd-418b-be71-feb34d9682a9","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:57:30.182Z","parentId":"2355d6ad-16e4-4ad3-a989-6568ae479faa"}
